SIMPLE: pluvial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pluvial
<hw>Plu"vi*al</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pluvialis</ets>, fr.
<ets>pluvia</ets> rain: cf. F. <ets>pluvial</ets>. See
<er>Plover</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to rain;
rainy.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Produced by the action of
rain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluvial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pluvial
<hw>Plu"vi*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>pluviale</ets> a
garment which keeps off the rain: cf. F. <ets>pluvial</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A priest's cope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluviameter</ent>⟦br⟧
